11:
For I, Wisdom, am more precious than jewels;
\q2 nothing you desire is as valuable as I am.
\q1

14:
I give good advice and I have the best wisdom; 
\q2 I have true understanding about the nature of things, and I have great strength.
\q1

15:
When kings are wise, they rule well;
\q2 and when rulers are wise, they make laws that are just.
\q1

16:
By me, Wisdom, rulers govern their people;
\q by me those who have authority guide their people with justice.
\q1

17:
I am Wisdom, and I love all who love me;
\q2 those who work hard to find me will find me.
\q1

22:
Yahweh created me, Wisdom; he made me when he began to create the world;
\q2 I was the first thing he created in the beginning.
\q1

30:
I was at Yahweh's side as his master craftsman;
\q1 I made him happy every day, and I always rejoiced when I was with him.
\q1

31:
I was delighted with the whole world he created;
\q2 I was happy with the people he brought into existence, too.
\q1
